# RAKSHA Enterprise Audio Emergency Dispatch Pipeline

## Overview

RAKSHA is an AI-powered emergency audio processing platform designed to analyze roadside emergency calls, extract structured crisis information, and route uncertain cases for human review.

The system combines speech-to-text transcription, audio enhancement, LLM-based emergency classification, structured data extraction, asynchronous processing, and audit-friendly quarantine workflows.

The project is built using a production-style architecture with FastAPI, Celery, PostgreSQL, Redis, MinIO, FFmpeg, Groq Whisper, and Llama 3.3.

---

## Key Features

### Emergency Audio Processing

* Upload roadside emergency audio recordings.
* Automatic audio normalization and cleaning.
* Noise filtering using FFmpeg.

### AI-Powered Speech Recognition

* Groq Whisper Large v3 transcription.
* Segment-level confidence analysis.
* No-speech probability validation.

### Structured Emergency Extraction

Extracts:

* Emergency severity
* Vehicle type
* Victim count
* Human review requirements
* Rejection reasons

### Human Review Workflow

Low-confidence or ambiguous audio is automatically quarantined for manual inspection.

### Asynchronous Processing

* Celery task queue
* Redis message broker
* Background processing workers

### Object Storage

* MinIO S3-compatible storage
* Audio archival
* Secure file handling

### Persistence Layer

* PostgreSQL database
* Structured extraction storage
* Quarantine audit records

### API Security

* API Key authentication
* Request validation
* Controlled endpoint access

